Resolve this story's narration scheme into exact character ids. The scheme
below is prose; downstream passes need the ids it means. You decide WHO the
narration follows — nothing else here is a judgment call.

POINT OF VIEW SCHEME: {{ vision.pov_hint or "one limited viewpoint" }}.

THE RETAINED CAST (ids are exact — copy them verbatim, never derive one from
a name):
{% for c in characters %}
- {{ c.id }} — {{ c.name }}: {{ c.concept }}
{% endfor %}

Return two fields:

- "heads": the characters whose heads the narration follows — the story's
  viewpoint roster. A single-viewpoint scheme names exactly ONE character
  (the scheme's protagonist — the perceiving center of the premise). A
  rotating scheme names each character the scheme rotates among: where it
  says "the suspects", "the crew", "each sibling", list those characters
  individually. Follow the scheme's own scope — do not add a character the
  scheme excludes (a victim, a bystander) and do not trim one it includes.
- "interlude_head": ONLY when the scheme names a deviant register — journal
  entries, letters, diary pages, recordings in a specific character's voice
  — the character who narrates that register. This may be a character NOT in
  "heads" (an investigator's journal amid rotating suspects is normal). When
  the scheme names no such register, return "".
